
Smashwords, Inc., based in Los Gatos, California, is an ebook selfpublishing and distribution platform that began public operation in 2008. It is a selfserve publishing service. Authors upload their manuscripts as Microsoft Word files to the Smashwords service, which converts the files into multiple ebook formats for reading on various ebook reading devices. Once published, the books are made available for sale online at a price set by the author. Smashwords does not use DRM. (From http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Smashwords wikipedia)

The Davis office is home to the bulk of Smashwords engineering staff.

